description:
Gap found: Late init failure cleanup not complete.

Why this was missed: Cleanup path analyzed but lichen_iface handling noted as intentional.

The actual bug: The fail_late_init label (lines 1028-1035) cleans up after late initialization failure. The comment at line 1015 says 'NOTE: Do NOT clear lichen_iface here - it has a set-once invariant'.

However, this creates a state where:
- lichen_iface is set (line 975)
- iface_init_failed is set (line 1035)
- link_ctx_initialized is 0 (line 1031)

If a subsequent initialization attempt is made (shouldn't happen, but if main calls lichen_l2_iface_init manually), the check at line 970-974 would fail:
  if (lichen_iface != NULL) {
      LOG_ERR('lichen_iface already set (set-once invariant violated)');
      atomic_set(&iface_init_failed, 1);
      return;
  }

So the failure state is permanent - no recovery without reboot.

This may be intentional (fail-safe), but the error message 'set-once invariant violated' is misleading in the late-init-failure case - the invariant wasn't violated, init just failed.

Priority 4 - error message clarity.
